arrillaga center for sports and recreation the stanford challenge arrillaga center for sports and recreation arrillaga center for sports and recreation completed in february 2006 the arrillaga center for sports & recreation is home to stanford's physical education and recreation programs as well as its varsity fencing and squash programs each day more than 1000 members of the campus community visit the 75000 square foot facility which features a fitness center basketball courts climbing wall squash courts fencing center state of the art sports medicine and human performance center and an academic resource center for varsity athletes learn more web site arrillaga center for sports & recreation comments are closed
